# What We've Built

Although the implementation is less than a hundred lines of code, we've built something surprisingly flexible.

Our EventBus can

- publish any event type
- register multiple listeners
- unregister listeners dynamically
- safely dispatch events
- remain completely decoupled from business logic

Even better, every service in our application can now share this single piece of infrastructure.

In the next article, we'll build a complete sample application around this EventBus with multiple listeners, services, and events. Then we'll explore its limitations and evolve it into an asynchronous EventBus capable of running listeners in parallel.
